{
  "video_id": "oidE2SSDczw",
  "title": "Kabuki: The people's dramatic art - Amanda Mattes",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 6999.0,
      "end_time": 9490.0,
      "text": "Many elements of traditional Japanese culture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 9490.0,
      "end_time": 11590.0,
      "text": "such as cuisine and martial arts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 11550.0,
      "end_time": 13586.0,
      "text": "are well-known throughout the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 13586.0,
      "end_time": 16412.0,
      "text": "Kabuki, a form of classical theater performance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 16412.0,
      "end_time": 18796.0,
      "text": "may not be as well understood in the West"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 18796.0,
      "end_time": 20753.0,
      "text": "but has evolved over 400 years"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 20753.0,
      "end_time": 24737.0,
      "text": "to still maintain influence and popularity to this day."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 24737.0,
      "end_time": 26186.0,
      "text": "The word Kabuki is derived"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 26186.0,
      "end_time": 28357.0,
      "text": "from the Japanese verb kabuku,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 28357.0,
      "end_time": 30958.0,
      "text": "meaning out of the ordinary or bizarre."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 30958.0,
      "end_time": 34339.0,
      "text": "Its history began in early 17th century Kyoto,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 34339.0,
      "end_time": 37235.0,
      "text": "where a shrine maiden named Izumo no Okuni"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 37235.0,
      "end_time": 40537.0,
      "text": "would use the city's dry Kamo Riverbed as a stage"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 40537.0,
      "end_time": 43468.0,
      "text": "to perform unusual dances for passerby,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 43468.0,
      "end_time": 45870.0,
      "text": "who found her daring parodies of Buddhist prayers"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 45870.0,
      "end_time": 48412.0,
      "text": "both entertaining and mesmerizing."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 48412.0,
      "end_time": 50217.0,
      "text": "Soon other troops began performing"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 50217.0,
      "end_time": 51545.0,
      "text": "in the same style,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 51545.0,
      "end_time": 53086.0,
      "text": "and Kabuki made history"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 53086.0,
      "end_time": 55549.0,
      "text": "as Japan's first dramatic performance form"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 55549.0,
      "end_time": 57498.0,
      "text": "catering to the common people."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 57498.0,
      "end_time": 59832.0,
      "text": "By relying on makeup, or keshou,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 59832.0,
      "end_time": 62296.0,
      "text": "and facial expressions instead of masks"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 62296.0,
      "end_time": 64380.0,
      "text": "and focusing on historical events"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 64379.99999999999,
      "end_time": 66739.0,
      "text": "and everyday life rather than folk tales,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 66739.0,
      "end_time": 68213.0,
      "text": "Kabuki set itself apart"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 68213.0,
      "end_time": 70270.0,
      "text": "from the upper-class dance theater form"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 70270.0,
      "end_time": 71552.0,
      "text": "known as Noh,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 71552.0,
      "end_time": 74131.0,
      "text": "and provided a unique commentary on society"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 74131.0,
      "end_time": 76113.0,
      "text": "during the Edo period."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 76113.0,
      "end_time": 78964.0,
      "text": "At first, the dance was practiced only by females"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 78964.0,
      "end_time": 82022.0,
      "text": "and commonly referred to as Onna-Kabuki."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 82022.0,
      "end_time": 84627.0,
      "text": "It soon evolved to an ensemble performance"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 84627.0,
      "end_time": 87049.0,
      "text": "and became a regular attraction at tea houses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 87049.0,
      "end_time": 89735.0,
      "text": "drawing audiences from all social classes."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 89735.0,
      "end_time": 92831.0,
      "text": "At this point, Onna-Kabuki was often risqu√©"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 92831.0,
      "end_time": 95293.0,
      "text": "as geishas performed not only to show off their singing and dancing abilities"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 96955.0,
      "end_time": 100384.0,
      "text": "but also to advertise their bodies to potential clients."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 100384.0,
      "end_time": 103462.0,
      "text": "A ban by the conservative Tokugawa shogunate"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 103462.0,
      "end_time": 104885.0,
      "text": "in 1629"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 104885.0,
      "end_time": 107660.0,
      "text": "led to the emergence of Wakashu-Kabuki"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 107660.0,
      "end_time": 109665.0,
      "text": "with young boys as actors."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 109665.0,
      "end_time": 112532.0,
      "text": "But when this was also banned for similar reasons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 112532.0,
      "end_time": 115121.0,
      "text": "there was a transition to Yaro-Kabuki,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 115121.0,
      "end_time": 116129.0,
      "text": "performed by men,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 116129.0,
      "end_time": 118577.0,
      "text": "necessitating elaborate costumes and makeup"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 118577.0,
      "end_time": 120548.0,
      "text": "for those playing female roles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 120548.0,
      "end_time": 121836.0,
      "text": "or onnagata."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 121836.0,
      "end_time": 123885.0,
      "text": "Attempts by the government to control Kabuki"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 123885.0,
      "end_time": 125754.0,
      "text": "didn't end with bans on the gender"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 125754.0,
      "end_time": 127599.0,
      "text": "or age of performers."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 127599.0,
      "end_time": 138584.0,
      "text": "The Tokugawa military group, or Bakufu, was fueled by Confucian ideals and often enacted sanctions on costume fabrics, stage weaponry, and the subject matter of the plot."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 138605.0,
      "end_time": 146152.0,
      "text": "At the same time, Kabuki became closely associated with and influenced by Bunraku, an elaborate form of puppet theater."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 146170.0,
      "end_time": 149912.0,
      "text": "Due to these influences, the once spontaneous,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 149964.0,
      "end_time": 153121.0,
      "text": "one-act dance evolved into a structured, five-act play"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 153121.0,
      "end_time": 156912.0,
      "text": "often based on the tenets of Confucian philosophy."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 156912.0,
      "end_time": 160652.0,
      "text": "Before 1868, when the Tokugawa shogunate fell"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 160652.0,
      "end_time": 162801.0,
      "text": "and Emperor Meiji was restored to power,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 162801.0,
      "end_time": 165670.0,
      "text": "Japan had practiced isolation from other countries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 165670.0,
      "end_time": 166915.0,
      "text": "or Sakoku."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 166915.0,
      "end_time": 168513.0,
      "text": "And thus, the development of Kabuki"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 168513.0,
      "end_time": 171497.0,
      "text": "had mostly been shaped by domestic influences."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 171497.0,
      "end_time": 173164.0,
      "text": "But even before this period,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 173164.0,
      "end_time": 175721.0,
      "text": "European artists, such as Claude Monet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 175721.0,
      "end_time": 177149.0,
      "text": "had become interested in"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 177149.0,
      "end_time": 178827.0,
      "text": "and inspired by Japanese art,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 178827.0,
      "end_time": 180642.0,
      "text": "such as woodblock prints,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 180642.0,
      "end_time": 182376.0,
      "text": "as well as live performance."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 182376.0,
      "end_time": 185497.0,
      "text": "After 1868, others such as Vincent van Gogh"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 185497.0,
      "end_time": 187571.0,
      "text": "and composer Claude Debussy"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 187571.0,
      "end_time": 190509.0,
      "text": "began to incorporate Kabuki influences in their work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 190509.0,
      "end_time": 192051.0,
      "text": "while Kabuki itself underwent"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 192051.0,
      "end_time": 193940.0,
      "text": "much change and experimentation"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 193940.0,
      "end_time": 196163.0,
      "text": "to adapt to the new modern era."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 196163.0,
      "end_time": 197892.0,
      "text": "Like other traditional art forms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 197892.0,
      "end_time": 199618.0,
      "text": "Kabuki suffered in popularity"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 199618.0,
      "end_time": 201411.0,
      "text": "in the wake of World War II."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 201411.0,
      "end_time": 202823.0,
      "text": "But innovation by artists"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 202823.0,
      "end_time": 205075.0,
      "text": "such as director Tetsuji Takechi"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 205075.0,
      "end_time": 207867.0,
      "text": "led to a resurgence shortly after."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 207867.0,
      "end_time": 209761.0,
      "text": "Indeed, Kabuki was even considered"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 209761.0,
      "end_time": 211332.0,
      "text": "a popular form of entertainment"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 211332.0,
      "end_time": 213731.0,
      "text": "amongst American troops stationed in Japan"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 213731.0,
      "end_time": 215767.0,
      "text": "despite initial U.S. censorship"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 215767.0,
      "end_time": 217555.0,
      "text": "of Japanese traditions."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 217555.0,
      "end_time": 219076.0,
      "text": "Today, Kabuki still lives on"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 219076.0,
      "end_time": 222334.0,
      "text": "as an integral part of Japan's rich cultural heritage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 222334.0,
      "end_time": 224495.0,
      "text": "extending its influence beyond the stage"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 224495.0,
      "end_time": 225320.0,
      "text": "to television,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 225320.0,
      "end_time": 225877.0,
      "text": "film,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 225877.0,
      "end_time": 226957.0,
      "text": "and anime."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 226957.0,
      "end_time": 232533.0,
      "text": "The art form pioneered by Okuni continues to delight audiences with the actors' elaborate makeup,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 232590.0,
      "end_time": 235596.0,
      "text": "extravagant and delicately embroidered costumes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 235596.0,
      "end_time": 237860.0,
      "text": "and the unmistakable melodrama"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 237860.0,
      "end_time": 247860.0,
      "text": "of the stories told on stage."
    }
  ]
}